			<h2 class="feature-title">
		  <a href="http://www.ipso-alliance.org/ipso-chairman-geoff-mulligan-named-as-presidential-innovation-fellow" title="Permalink to June 21, 2013 &#8211; IPSO CHAIRMAN Geoff Mulligan Named as Presidential Innovation Fellow" rel="bookmark">June 21, 2013 &#8211; IPSO CHAIRMAN Geoff Mulligan Named as Presidential Innovation Fellow</a>
                </h2>
		<div class="entry-content">
			<p> Geoff Mulligan, Chairman of the IPSO Board of Directors, has been named as a Presidential Innovation Fellow working on the Cyber-Physical Systems project at the National Institute of Standards and Technology. Geoff (Proto6) is a technology consultant focused on the Internet of Things, RF Sensors, IPv6, IP networks and open systems. He helped design IPv6 &hellip; <a href="http://www.ipso-alliance.org/ipso-chairman-geoff-mulligan-named-as-presidential-innovation-fellow">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
